{
  "stem": "24814.1",
  "chunk_idx": 7,
  "model": "openai/gpt-oss-120b",
  "elapsed_s": 5.1,
  "sentences_input": [
    {
      "segment_idx": 55,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 4,
      "text": "In fact, there was a movie made about-- that showed Dachau, a popular movie and I can't remember who all was in it, based on a novel by an English novelist.",
      "word_count": 31
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 55,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 5,
      "text": "Nobody had any idea of the extent of the killing that was going on, the scale was what we-- we knew that there were-- that people-- that the treatment of Jews was, of course, brutal, that they were, to use a loose word, discriminated against, and that they were losing their property, that they were put into camps.",
      "word_count": 58
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 55,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 6,
      "text": "And that's about as far as anybody knew.",
      "word_count": 8
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 55,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 7,
      "text": "The-- the organized killing that went on was kind of a secret in the Western world, at least to me and my friends.",
      "word_count": 23
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 56,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 0,
      "text": "Pardon?",
      "word_count": 1
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 57,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 0,
      "text": "We shipped over in September, '44.",
      "word_count": 6
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 58,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 0,
      "text": "Oh, it was a liberating ship.",
      "word_count": 6
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 58,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 1,
      "text": "Who knows what?",
      "word_count": 3
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 58,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 2,
      "text": "They were little squat tubs that we sailed across.",
      "word_count": 9
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 58,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 3,
      "text": "We sailed in a convoy, escorted by Canadian Corvettes, which are like in a cruiser.",
      "word_count": 15
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 58,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 4,
      "text": "And we were shadowed by a German submarine wolfpack most of the way, and we could hear the depth bombs going off against the ships.",
      "word_count": 25
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 58,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 5,
      "text": "We landed in England.",
      "word_count": 4
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 58,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 6,
      "text": "And our division reassembled at the old British cavalry barracks near Salisbury, England, Salisbury Plain, classical military place.",
      "word_count": 18
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 58,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 7,
      "text": "We spent a month in England picking up new tanks with higher velocity guns and retraining, and then we crossed the Channel, landed at Cherbourg.",
      "word_count": 25
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 58,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 8,
      "text": "And Eisenhower couldn't quite decide which place-- which way to send our division.",
      "word_count": 13
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 58,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 9,
      "text": "First, we heard we were going up north to Holland.",
      "word_count": 10
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 58,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 10,
      "text": "But then they decided to send us in the big chase across France, chasing the Germans toward the German border.",
      "word_count": 20
    }
  ],
